{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KtSeQedAoCzmZZoNsiaMLj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the ops-user also can't authenticate. Let me test with the elastic user (the built-in user).\n\nThe key insight now is:\n1. The StatefulSet has an `emptyDir` volume for `es-users` (containing `users` and `users_roles` files)\n2. The init container `set-elastic-password` writes only `elastic:$(password)` to the users file\n3. Neither `ops-user` nor `report-user` are in the file realm that's actually mounted on the pods\n4. Both `es-file-realm-aggregate` and `user-provided-file-realm` secrets are not mounted anywhere on the pods\n5. The task is to merge `user-provided-file-realm` into `es-file-realm-aggregate` and mount it on the pods\n\nThe challenge is that switching from the emptyDir to a mounted secret means losing the elastic user setup from the init container, though that's fine since elastic is a built-in user managed through a different mechanism in Elasticsearch.\n\nThe file realm files live at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users` and `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users_roles`. The init container currently writes the elastic user there, but in Elasticsearch 8.x the elastic user is actually a built-in user handled by the native realm, not the file realm, so having it in the file realm might be redundant or unnecessary.\n\nTo fix authentication for `report-user`, I need to merge the `users` and `users_roles` files from both secrets and update the `es-file-realm-aggregate` secret with the merged content. Then the StatefulSet needs to mount this secret so Elasticsearch uses it for the file realm instead of relying on the emptyDir and init container approach. This would require a rolling restart, but given the case name references file-realm-user-roles-merge, that's likely the intended solution. es-file-realm-aggregate` on the StatefulSet pods, then the elastic user will continue working through the native realm while report-user works through the file realm. Now I need to decode these secrets to see what's actually in them.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3107,"cache_read_input_tokens":36004,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3107},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c656a6e4-a5db-4687-8cb3-0e9353c86e23","uuid":"d6d54c30-6dd4-44e1-af36-5931e5a637aa","request_id":"req_011Cc9YGBJe3qsGhGQQaAknv"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KtSeQedAoCzmZZoNsiaMLj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01SDu75qr52MoDD6peHocu8K","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"export KUBECONFIG=/mydata/karma/runs/long-examples/elasticsearch-long-all-cases-marathon-20260617_205721/bundle/kubeconfig\n\n# Decode aggregate secret\necho \"=== es-file-realm-aggregate ===\"\necho \"users:\"\nkubectl -n elasticsearch get secret es-file-realm-aggregate -o jsonpath='{.data.users}' | base64 -d\necho \"---\"\necho \"users_roles:\"\nkubectl -n elasticsearch get secret es-file-realm-aggregate -o jsonpath='{.data.users_roles}' | base64 -d\necho \"---\"\necho \"\"\necho \"=== user-provided-file-realm ===\"\necho \"users:\"\nkubectl -n elasticsearch get secret user-provided-file-realm -o jsonpath='{.data.users}' | base64 -d\necho \"---\"\necho \"users_roles:\"\nkubectl -n elasticsearch get secret user-provided-file-realm -o jsonpath='{.data.users_roles}' | base64 -d","description":"Decode both file realm secrets to see their content"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3107,"cache_read_input_tokens":36004,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3107},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c656a6e4-a5db-4687-8cb3-0e9353c86e23","uuid":"0f1c9c07-935c-416d-8f8f-d38fa78854a6","request_id":"req_011Cc9YGBJe3qsGhGQQaAknv"}
