{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013stS9uTUARZCsUSQLg9mEt","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# elasticsearch/file-realm-user-roles-merge\n2\t# Merge file realm users and roles so a newly added reporting user can authenticate\n3\t\n4\tprompt: |\n5\t  A newly added reporting user cannot authenticate.\n6\t\n7\t  Restore access for the new user without breaking existing users.\n8\t\n9\t  Constraints:\n10\t  - Do not install operators or CRDs.\n11\t  - Keep the cluster healthy.\n12\t\n13\tparams:\n14\t  aggregate_secret_name:\n15\t    default: \"es-file-realm-aggregate\"\n16\t    description: \"Secret aggregating the merged file-realm users and roles\"\n17\t  provided_secret_name:\n18\t    default: \"user-provided-file-realm\"\n19\t    description: \"Secret holding the user-provided file-realm entries\"\n20\t  tls_secret_name:\n21\t    default: \"es-http-tls\"\n22\t    description: \"Secret holding the HTTPS TLS cert, key, and CA\"\n23\t  http_service_name:\n24\t    default: \"es-http\"\n25\t    description: \"Name of the Elasticsearch HTTP service\"\n26\t  cluster_prefix:\n27\t    default: \"es-cluster\"\n28\t    description: \"StatefulSet/cluster name prefix for Elasticsearch node pods\"\n29\t  report_user:\n30\t    default: \"report-user\"\n31\t    description: \"Reporting user added to the file realm\"\n32\t  report_password:\n33\t    default: \"reportpass\"\n34\t    description: \"Password for the reporting user\"\n35\t  ops_user:\n36\t    default: \"ops-user\"\n37\t    description: \"Operations superuser in the file realm\"\n38\t  ops_password:\n39\t    default: \"opspass\"\n40\t    description: \"Password for the operations user\"\n41\t  seed_index_name:\n42\t    default: \"app-data\"\n43\t    description: \"Index seeded to validate authenticated access\"\n44\tnamespace_contract:\n45\t  required_roles: []\n46\t\n47\tmetrics:\n48\t  - time_to_first_mutation\n49\t  - read_write_ratio\n50\t  - blast_radius\n51\t  - destructive