{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FtAX6ohmkUfSkAgoxikY8j","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `app-data` index doesn't exist. This was supposed to be seeded by the precondition (ops-user needs to authenticate to create it), but ops-user can't authenticate either. So both issues need to be fixed:\n\n1. Merge report-user into `es-file-realm-aggregate`\n2. Mount the aggregate secret on the pods (so both users can authenticate)\n3. Create the app-data index (so report-user can read it)\n\nLet me plan the execution:\n\n**Step 1: Merge the two file realm secrets**\nI need to decode both secrets, combine their users and users_roles files, and update `es-file-realm-aggregate` with the merged content.\n\n**Step 2: Update StatefulSet to mount the aggregate secret**\nI'll add a new volume from the `es-file-realm-aggregate` secret and configure the volumeMounts to reference the users and users_roles files from this volume.\n\n**Step 3: Wait for rolling restart**\nThe pods will restart with the new secret mounted.\n\n**Step 4: Create app-data index and seed it**\nOnce ops-user can authenticate, I'll create the index. Let me also check the statefulset.yaml to understand the current configuration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1375,"cache_read_input_tokens":53063,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1375},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c656a6e4-a5db-4687-8cb3-0e9353c86e23","uuid":"60ecc660-a1bc-48be-9658-a4e62fb3496a","request_id":"req_011Cc9YQnxUS5n3x4gvqD4Mc"}
